==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Credulous
<hw>Cred"u*lous</hw> <pr>(kr?d"?-l?s; 135)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>credulus</ets>, fr. <ets>credere</ets>. See <er>Creed</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Apt to believe on slight evidence; easily imposed upon;
unsuspecting.</def> <rj><au>Landor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Eve, our <qex>credulous</qex> mother.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Believed too readily.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Credulously</ent>⟦br⟧
